@52   = ~The arrow of piercing is long and thin, imbued with magical properties that allow it to "push" itself through armor, striking out towards the heart of the victim. Once the arrow penetrates all the way through a creature, it flies out, potentially hitting another creature. Since the arrow continues to apply force even after it hits the target, it deals piercing damage rather than missile damage, and spells that normally block or reflect missile attacks such as Physical Mirror and Entropy Shield do not stop this arrow.

