@206  = ~Giant's Sleep +5~
@207  = ~This weapon was used by the human ranger Althax Grom. Althax hated the giants that plagued his homeland and was trained to exterminate them from a young age. Although Althax originally fought his foes using the sword and bow, he quickly decided that those weapons were too slow against his huge foes. His druid friend, Eladan, enchanted this hammer for him. The reputation of the weapon grew as legends of Althax grew. Even though the war hammer has passed through many hands since Althax's untimely demise, Giant's Sleep will always be remembered as the weapon of that powerful warrior.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
- Wearer is immune to pushing and pulling effects

Combat abilities:
- When a giant is hit by this weapon, it takes crushing damage equal to 10% of its maximum hit points

THAC0: +5
Damage: 1d4+6 (crushing)
Speed Factor: 0
Proficiency Type: War Hammer
Type: One-handed
Requires:
 9 Strength

