- Intelligence: +2

Weight: 0~
@308  = ~This ioun stone has had many owners over the centuries, from the thief who carried it as a good luck charm to the ogre who thought it to be the world's smallest crystal ball. It was once even used by a gnome as a prosthetic eye, although its properties did not improve her vision. Eventually the stone fell into the hands of a group of elven wizards. It is uncertain whether it was used for research purposes or merely worn for protection against hostile magic. Unlike common ioun stones, this one appears to be colorless and almost entirely transparent.

